#week-title("Three", "Post Nubila Phoebus: After the Clouds, the Sun")

=== Core Teaching

*Post nubila phoebus* — after the clouds, the sun. This is the motto of the
alchemist who continues.

It is not a promise of triumph or a guarantee of arrival. It is a statement of
the practitioner's disposition in the face of the Work's inherent uncertainty:
the clouds are present; they have been present throughout three years; they will
continue to be present. The sun exists behind them, always. The practitioner who
knows this does not require the sun to be constantly visible in order to continue
the Work.

The curriculum ends not with a completion but with a beginning. The preparations
underway will continue. The journals will continue. The daily laboratory visits
will continue. The long-work logs will continue, recording the slow colour
changes in sealed vessels that will not reach their culmination for months or
years after the curriculum's formal close.

*What the Adept carries forward.* From the curriculum:

- An active Plant Stone, however advanced
- At least one ongoing mineral Via Humida preparation
- A long circulation, still circulating
- A personal alchemical practice: laboratory, journal, nature vigil, inner work
- An understanding of the three principles, the planetary correspondences, the
  seasonal rhythms, and the philosophical framework of Paracelsian alchemy

None of this disappears when the curriculum ends. It deepens. The teacher
becomes a companion. The student becomes a practitioner. The curriculum becomes
a foundation.

*The DES-3 integration as the ongoing inner work.* DES-3's cognitive-behavioural
approach — the integration of inner insights into the habitual texture of daily
life — is the work of years, not months. The practitioner who has done the
Desoille work honestly across three years is not "finished" with the inner
work; they have built the instrument. The instrument is now used in the context
of actual life: the laboratory, the community, the relationships, the ongoing
practice.

=== Topics This Week

- *Post nubila phoebus* as the practitioner's stance in relation to the Work
- What the Adept carries forward: active preparations, practice, understanding
- The teacher becoming companion; the student becoming practitioner
- DES-3 as the ongoing inner work: instrument built, now used

